# {{lb|en|Hinduism}} An ancient [[Indian]] [[genre]] (or a group of related genres) of [[Hindu]] or [[Jain]] literature (as distinct from oral tradition). They are primarily post-[[Vedic]] texts containing a narrative of the history of the Universe, from creation to destruction, genealogies of the kings, heroes and demigods, and descriptions of Hindu cosmology, philosophy and geography.

